# ECC-vendored language rules (common/ cpp/ python/ rust/ typescript/ web/) are
# installer-managed: ecc-install / ecc-update re-vendor them from the ECC repo
# via `cp -R`, byte-identical to upstream. They are reproducible and not ours,
# so they live on disk but stay untracked -- the same model already used for ECC
# skills (claude/skills/.gitignore) and ECC commands/agents/hooks.
#
# Only our OWN custom rules are version-controlled. Put them under
# claude/rules/personal/ (outside the ECC lang dirs, which ecc-sync-rules wipes
# with `rm -rf` on every sync) and they are tracked by the whitelist below.
/*
!/.gitignore
!/personal/
